CHAT.comment: At first Mot thinks she's the one who is supposed to write the letter. She provides Chi with all of the content. Mot asks Chi what he liked most about the book , but Chi doesn't have much to say on the subject. Mot begins to read the story , and Chi writes about the part Mot likes. Later Mot asks Chi to continue reading the story where she left off. She corrects him when he makes a mistake in his reading. After hearing the whole story she thinks of another sentence to add to the letter. Interestingly , when Chi reads the finished letter out loud , he corrects some of the mistakes in Mot's dictation.

u.a: field notes say that Mot puts a hyphen in the letter for Chi . She does so where the word caterpillar extends onto the next line
MOT is reading the story to herself
MOT reads the first two sentences of the story to herself again
MOT continues to read the book to herself
MOT says something to herself as she goes to get her glasses
Chi whispers to himself as he writes
